# --- workbay-bootstrap-managed surfaces ---------------------------------
# Everything below is regenerated by `workbay-bootstrap install` from the
# pinned `remote_sha` recorded in `.workbay-bootstrap.json` (which IS tracked
# — it's the install ledger). Do not commit these surfaces:
#   - SHARED entries are symlinks into `.workbay/remote/`; they break on a
#     fresh clone until bootstrap recreates the cache.
#   - GENERATED entries are deterministic outputs of the workflow generator
#     and the MCP-config writer; committing them produces drift on every
#     `bootstrap update`.
# The same rule applies to dogfood installs (this monorepo consuming
# itself) and external client installs.

# disposable remote-clone cache (the whole dir, not just remote/)
.workbay/

# SHARED surfaces (symlinks → .workbay/remote/...)
# implementation note S3: /scripts/hooks is now a TRACKED in-tree symlink into the
# co-located payload (see `make dogfood-link`) so a fresh clone self-wires git
# hooks with no bootstrap — it is intentionally NOT ignored here.
/.github/hooks
/docs/workbay/contracts
/docs/workbay/rules
/docs/workbay/templates
/Makefile.d
/scripts/workbay
# internal: Codex hook config — shared file surface (generated golden in
# the workbay-system payload, symlinked here by install/adopt).
/.codex/hooks.json

# GENERATED surfaces (real dirs/files written by the workflow generator)
/.github/prompts/

# implementation note: generator_input surfaces (regenerated every install; self-host is exempt from the consumer block)
/scripts/generate_agent_workflows.py
/config/agent-workflows/portable_commands.json
/skills

# Grok plugin tree — no marketplace indirection, so the full tree is
# re-materialized from effective/grok on every install/update (internal).
# Same regenerable-content rule as the generated surfaces above.
/.grok/plugins/workbay-system

# implementation note S2: generated adapter artifacts at the package source-of-truth.
# Regenerated deterministically from skills/ + the workflow manifest by
# `make generate` (and at consumer install time). Committing them re-introduces
# the silent-drift class implementation note hit; only the SKILL.md sources + manifests
# stay in git. `check-agent-workflows` regenerates and verifies a clean build.
/packages/workbay-system/.github/prompts/

# Local settings
/.claude/settings.local.json
/.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# GENERATED MCP-server configs
/.mcp.json
/.vscode/mcp.json
/.codex/config.toml

# local handoff state (per-checkout SQLite)
.task-state/

# on-demand local handoff snapshots; rendered from the handoff DB on demand
/CURRENT_TASK.json
/DASHBOARD.txt

# IDE
.cursor/

# Materialized harness plugin surface (regenerated by `workbay-bootstrap install`;
# source = workbay-system payload + materialize_grok_plugin). Mirrors .cursor/.
.grok/
/CLAUDE.local.md

# Generated per-lane orchestration manifests (machine-local; embed absolute worktree
# paths that die with the lane). Regenerated by the orchestrator; never source.
# Keep the tracked example fixture.
config/lane-orchestration/*.json
!config/lane-orchestration/example-multi-lane-task.json
